Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Remove the dark green top and the bottom root from the @leek{2}. Cut in half lengthways, then slice into thin half moon shapes. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Remove the core from the @red pepper{2}(core removed) and chop into small 1cm chunks. Chop the @chives{1}(chopped into ½cm pieces) into ½cm pieces.

> Tip: Use scissors to chop chives if you want!

Put a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat and drizzle in some @oil{drizzle}. Add your leek and pepper and cook for ~{5%minutes} until softened.

> Tip: Don't worry if they colour slightly, this will just add to the flavour!

While your veggies are cooking, remove the sausage meat from its skin (discard the skin) from the @spiced pork sausage{8} and drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{2}.

Once your leek and pepper are soft, add your sausage meat to the pan. Cook for ~{5%minutes}, use a #spoon{} to break it up while it cooks. Once your sausage meat has cooked for 5 mins and is browned, add a good pinch of @salt{good pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{}. Add in your garlic, @smoked paprika{1} and @ground cumin{1}. Mix together and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Pour the @chopped tomatoes{2} into the pan. Refill your tin(s) a quarter with water and add to the pan as well. Add the @beef stock pot{2} and stir until dissolved, then add your kidney beans. Stir together and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}, until your chilli is thick and tomatoey.

While your chilli cooks, make your tortilla chips! Using some #scissors{}, cut each @super soft tortilla with whole wheat{4} into eight triangles.

> We used one tortilla per person but if you want to use two per person, that's fine - you have enough!

Place your chips on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer and drizzle over some @olive oil{drizzle}. Sprinkle over a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{grind} and pop in your oven for ~{4-5%minutes}.

> Tip: Keep an eye on them to make sure they don't burn!

Taste your chilli and add more salt and pepper if necessary. Serve your chilli in #bowls{} with a spoonful of @Greek style natural yoghurt{2} on top and a sprinkling of chives. Place your tortilla chips on the side of the bowl (for scooping purposes) and enjoy!